claim: "Thou shalt not steal" is one of the foundational moral imperatives of the Torah, the central body of ethical and religious codes of Judaism.
premise_source_doc_sentence: `` Thou shalt not steal '' is one of the Ten Commandments of the Torah  (  and by extension the Old Testament  )  , which are widely understood as moral imperatives by legal scholars , Jewish scholars , Catholic scholars , and Post-Reformation scholars .
